% ============================================================
% references.bib
% Provenance and research sources for the VVUQ-04 draft-bill (LaTeX).
%
% A finished congressional amendment carries no bibliography; its operative text
% cites authority inline by United States Code and Public Law numbers. This file
% backs only the research-aid back matter (the Provenance and Research Sources
% appendix and, when drafted, the findings and the research-influence matrix),
% so the operative sections stay clean while every source remains auditable.
%
% House conventions (carried from the template-bill and the instruct-bill .bib
% files): a bare doi field where a DOI exists; a resolver or canonical url; a
% note that opens with "DOI: <doi>." when a DOI exists and ends with the
% clickable link in \url{...}; no howpublished field; no duplicate link across
% the set. Rendered with ieeetr, which prints the note. Operative-authority keys
% mirror the keys used in papers/VVUQ-04/instruct-bill so a future pass can
% resolve them without renaming.
% ============================================================

